HEADWORD: Acerb
<hw>A*cerb"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acerbus</ets>, fr. <ets>acer</ets> sharp: cf. F. <ets>acerbe</ets>.
See <er>Acrid</er>.]</ety> <def>Sour, bitter, and harsh to the taste, as
unripe fruit; sharp and harsh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

